### Create a task (lesson 3)
POST http://localhost:3000/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Learn Express",
  "description": "Build a task manager API"
}

### Get all tasks (lesson 3)
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks

### LESSON 12

### Get first page (default: 20 per page)
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks

### Get 5 per page, page 1
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks?page=1&limit=5

### Get page 2
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks?page=2&limit=5

### Only completed tasks
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks?completed=true

### Only incomplete tasks
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks?completed=false

### Search for "grocery" (should find 2 tasks)
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks?search=grocery

### Combine: incomplete tasks sorted by title A-Z
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks?completed=false&sort=title&order=asc

### Combine everything: search + filter + sort + paginate
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks?search=learn&completed=false&sort=title&order=asc&page=1&limit=5

### Bad params (should get 400)
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks?page=-1

### Bad sort column (should get 400)
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks?sort=password

### Lesson 13

### Step 1: Get Google login URL
GET http://localhost:3000/auth/google

### Step 2: Copy the URL from the response, open it in your browser,
### log in with Google, and you'll be redirected to /auth/callback
### with tokens in the response.

### Step 3: Use the access_token to hit protected routes
GET http://localhost:3000/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### Step 4: Create a task as the authenticated user
POST http://localhost:3000/tasks
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "title": "My first authenticated task"
}

### Step 5: Get your tasks (only yours will show)
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### Step 6: Try without a token (should get 401)
GET http://localhost:3000/tasks